        <updateDate>2009-06-24T21:08:35Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Credit Score Fairness Act of 2009 - Amends the Fair Credit Reporting Act to require: (1) each consumer reporting agency to make credit scores available to consumers once each year without charge; and (2) certain creditors (other than mortgage lenders) to disclose consumer credit scores that were used in making any determination with respect to extending the consumer credit.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
